  <title>GObject.TypeInfo</title>
  <synopsis><code>
const GObject = imports.gi.GObject;

let typeInfo = new GObject.TypeInfo({
    <link xref='GObject.TypeInfo-class_size'>class_size</link>: value
    <link xref='GObject.TypeInfo-instance_size'>instance_size</link>: value
    <link xref='GObject.TypeInfo-n_preallocs'>n_preallocs</link>: value
});
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>This structure is used to provide the type system with the information
required to initialize and destruct (finalize) a type's class and
its instances.
The initialized structure is passed to the <link xref="GObject.type_register_static"/> function
(or is copied into the provided <link xref="GObject.TypeInfo"/> structure in the
<link xref="GObject.complete_type_info"/>). The type system will perform a deep
copy of this structure, so its memory does not need to be persistent
across invocation of <link xref="GObject.type_register_static"/>.</p>

